git and GitHub

Git is version control system.

we have created the git repo: To create a git repo which command we will use?

git init--> .git(subdirectory)

Local git repo (which you will create on your development box)

Remote git repo (which will be shared across multiple developers, which you create on GitHub)


-->If I create a file, I want to staged that file for commit-> git add

--> We create the commit: git commit -m "Add"

-->commit id (Version id)-->track the code changes

